reviews.review_text: - Great recording, just a bit on the tinny side (easily fixed). The first set is excellent & nicely psychedelic with lots of delay on the vocals. Pre-drums half of second set is less inspired, though I have to say Brent's new song kinda kicks ass. Last part is good. Four stars, mostly for the first set.

ThirtyONE years ago! Hampton! Tropical Weather and two hot shows.  This second night, after listening to this fine recording, is pretty damn good-better than I remember it as I was behind the SBD in the pit.  FOB is the way to go at Hampton.
